  {
    "id": "the_lost_tapes",
    "title": "the lost tapes",
    "year": "2008",
    "cover": "https://drewprototypes.s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/drew-waters-music.com/album_images/shotwell_waters.png",
    "notes": "\nfound this a couple of days ago going through my gear space. i'm not sure why i didn't publish this. at the time, 18 years ago now, the only format was cd, possibly a dedicated website, maybe that's why? these tracks were contained on an old alesis masterlink, like the only cool piece of gear they ever made.\n<br>\nblew my mind in a couple of ways in that i continue to do bass/drum duets and this was the first.\n<br>\nthe arrangements are bolder than i expected. the composed sections, soloing, transcribing the solo then composing a harmonization, were a little startling. it really inspires me to do more of this.\n<br>\ni was mixing out of the box for the first time, had no clue what i was doing really. just a digi003 through a folcrom passive mixer, printing to the masterlink, in a space in san leandro.\n<br>\nsome originals and favorite standards. especially beatrice. that piece is all magic.\n",
    "credits": "\n        <div class=\"dw-credits-title\">credits</div>\n        <div class=\"dw-credit-line\">drew waters · guitar, recording, production</div>\n        <div class=\"dw-credit-line\">joe shotwell · drums</div>\n        <div class=\"dw-credit-line\">recorded at sharkbite studios, oakland, 2008</div>\n      ",
    "tracks": [
